s/apjs489210f3", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/210/2/23/apjs489210f3_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs489210f3", "figure_label": "Figure 3.", "figure_caption": "Comparison of the observed (upper) and simulated (lower) spectra of the &Delta;<italic>v</italic>&nbsp;&equals; &minus;1 sequence of the <italic>A</italic><sup>2</sup>&Pi;&ndash;<italic>X</italic><sup>2</sup>&Sigma;<sup>+</sup> transition of CN. The unmarked emission lines near the 6&ndash;7 and 7&ndash;8 bands are vibration&ndash;rotation lines of the 2&ndash;0 overtone of HCl, present as an impurity. The absence of 5&ndash;6 band in both spectra is consistent with the very small Franck&ndash;Condon factor calculated by <sc>level</sc>."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs489210f4", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs489210f4", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/210/2/23/apjs489210f4_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs489210f4", "figure_label": "Figure 4.", "figure_caption": "Comparison of a part of the observed (upper) and simulated (lower) spectra of the <italic>A</italic><sup>2</sup>&Pi;&ndash;<italic>X</italic><sup>2</sup>&Sigma;<sup>+</sup>, 0&ndash;1 band near the <italic>R</italic><sub>2</sub> head showing a very good correspondence between the two spectra."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs489210f5", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs489210f5", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/210/2/23/apjs489210f5_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs489210f5", "figure_label": "Figure 5.", "figure_caption": "Comparison of the observed (upper) and simulated (lower) spectra of the <italic>A</italic><sup>2</sup>&Pi;&ndash;<italic>X</italic><sup>2</sup>&Sigma;<sup>+</sup>, 1&ndash;0, <italic><sup>s</sup>R</italic><sub>21</sub> branch."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs489210f6", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs489210f6", "thumbnail": "https://s3.ama