yeSED code compared with that obtained with the FAST code by Muzzin et al. (2013). The parameter is estimated with the mean of the posterior distribution. The probability density distribution of the difference between the results of the two codes is shown in the lower panel. At the top of the figure, the mean, the dispersion, and the fraction of outliers with a difference larger than 3&sigma; are shown."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs501267f28", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs501267f28", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/215/1/2/apjs501267f28_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs501267f28", "figure_label": "Figure 28.", "figure_caption": "Similar to Figure 27, but for the <italic>e</italic>-folding time tau."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs501267f29", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs501267f29", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/215/1/2/apjs501267f29_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs501267f29", "figure_label": "Figure 29.", "figure_caption": "Similar to Figure 27, but for the dust extinction <italic>A<sub>v</sub></italic>."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs501267f30", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs501267f30", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/215/1/2/apjs501267f30_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs501267f30", "figure_label": "Figure 30.", "figure_caption": "Similar to Figure 27, but for the stellar mass."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs501267f31", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs501267f31", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/215/1/2/apjs501267f31_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs501267f31", "figure_label": "Figure 31.", "figure_caption": "Similar to Figure 27, but for the star formation rate."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs501267f32", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs501267f32", "thumbnail": "https://s