.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs498940f11", "figure_label": "Figure 11.", "figure_caption": "Convergence for the 3D circularly polarized Alfv&eacute;n-Whistler wave test using finite differencing in Hall-MHD. Reconstruction is performed using the MP5 algorithm, and currents are obtained by fourth-order central differences Equation&nbsp;(47) and time stepping with SSPRK(5, 4), yielding over-all fourth-order accuracy (left panel). The right panel shows diagonal cuts in wave direction <inline-formula><tex-math><?CDATA $\\\\mathbf {\\\\hat{k}}$?></tex-math><inline-graphic xmlns:xlink=\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\" xlink:href=\\"apjs498940ieqn25.gif\\"/></inline-formula> of <italic>B<sub>z</sub></italic> at <italic>t</italic> &equals; 0 (black) and <italic>t</italic> &equals; <italic>P</italic> (gray) for the two resolutions <italic>N<sub>x</sub></italic> &equals; 32 (dashes) and <italic>N<sub>x</sub></italic> &equals; 64 (dots)."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs498940f12", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs498940f12", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/214/1/4/apjs498940f12_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs498940f12", "figure_label": "Figure 12.", "figure_caption": "Interference pattern resulting from the Friedrich wave diagram test with Hall-MHD. Top panel: out-of-plane velocity (left) and pressure (right). Bottom panel: analytic Hall-MHD group diagram for <italic>kd</italic> &equals; 10 for Alfv&eacute;n-type (solid) and fast-type (dashed) waves. One can clearly recognize the enveloping fast-type and Alfv&eacute;n-type wave families."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs498940f13", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs498940f13", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/214/1/4/apjs498940f13_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs498940f13", "figure_label": "Figure 13.", "figure_caption": "Vertical current <italic>j<sub>z</sub></italic> in the Hall double