com/aasie/images/0067-0049/212/2/18/apjs492953f3_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs492953f3", "figure_label": "Figure 3.", "figure_caption": "Difference between measured and synthesized <italic>W</italic>4 magnitudes for galaxies drawn from our sample, plotted as a function of &sim;22&thinsp;&mu;m spectral index. The pre-launch <italic>WISE</italic> <italic>W</italic>4 filter curves does not match the on-sky performance (Wright et al. 2010; Jarrett et al. 2013), so the measured <italic>W</italic>4 magnitudes are systematically too bright for galaxies with spectra that differ significantly from the Rayleigh&ndash;Jeans approximation."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs492953f4", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs492953f4", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/212/2/18/apjs492953f4_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs492953f4", "figure_label": "Figure 4.", "figure_caption": "Optical color&ndash;magnitude diagram for galaxies in our sample along with <italic>g</italic> &lt; 14 galaxies from the NASA-Sloan Atlas. Symbols are a function of RC3 morphological T-Type (de Vaucouleurs et al. 1991), and sample galaxies that are not in the RC3 have almost exclusively irregular and peculiar morphologies. Our sample spans the range of observed colors for <italic>z</italic> &sim; 0 galaxies and a broad range of absolute magnitudes."}, {"images": [{"image_id": "apjs492953f5", "highres": "http://www.astroexplorer.org/details/apjs492953f5", "thumbnail": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/aasie/images/0067-0049/212/2/18/apjs492953f5_tb.jpg", "format": "jpg"}], "figure_id": "apjs492953f5", "figure_label": "Figure 5.", "figure_caption": "<italic>u</italic>&thinsp;&minus;&thinsp;<italic>g</italic> and <italic>g</italic>&thinsp;&minus;&thinsp;<italic>r</italic> colors of galaxies from our sample (colored symbols), along with <italic>g</italic> &lt; 14 galaxies from the NASA-Sloan Atlas (gray points). The left panel shows the observed 